Sorting vs Clustering

Sometimes terms overlap.


---

Sorting

Rows ordered physically.


---

Clustering

Broader optimization concept using ordering/grouping.


---

Example

ORDER BY customer_id

creates sorted organization.

Warehouse engines use this internally for clustering optimization.


---

Benefits of Clustering ⭐

1. Faster Filtering

Less block scanning.
---
2. Better Compression
Similar values grouped together.
---

3. Faster Aggregations
Grouped rows easier to process.
---

4. Reduced Query Cost

Especially in cloud warehouses.
---

Disadvantages ⚠️
1. Maintenance Cost
New data may disrupt clustering.
---
2. Re-Clustering Overhead

Warehouse may need reorganizing.
---

3. Wrong Clustering Columns Hurt Performance

Poor choices reduce benefit.
---

Important Interview Insight ⭐

Choose clustering columns based on frequent query filtering patterns.

Very important statement.


